Rating: 4
I must tell you that those who ate this recipe instantly became very protective of it. I brought it to a friendly barbecue and my boyfriend purposely avoided talking about it in the hopes that there would be more leftovers for him to eat later. He kept asking where it was on our drive home. An instant hit... But, as others have said, it needs some tweeking: I used multi-colored pasta, along with sherry cooking wine instead of vinegar, a slight amount of unseasoned rice vinegar, olive oil instead of vegetable oil (??? There's pasta here, people! Why wouldn't they have automatically used olive oil in the first place?!), sliced black olives, double the garlic, and a whole shallot. The other difference is that I emulsified the garlic and the shallots, which added the flavor without making the chunks of either overpowering. Next time, I would make a second batch of the dressing to add right before serving, as the pasta does absorb most of the dressing while overnighting in the fridge.

