Rating: 3
The recipe as it's listed here is just a starting point. The beauty of a pasta salad is that it's a perfect foil for so many flavor combinations. I used extra virgin olive oil for the dressing and threw in some chopped shallots. Instead of mozzarella, I used a thick-cut slice of provolone from the store deli (much cheaper than smoked mozzarella and pretty tasty.) I also used sun-dried tomatoes packed in olive oil and whole wheat rotini. The whole wheat pasta doesn't taste dramatically different from the regular and it packs in some extra fiber (which we could all use more of!). I also added canned artichokes hearts, kalamata olives and some chopped fresh parsley. What I got was a very tasty, hearty salad perfect for a quick lunch.

